Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @butter{20%g} from your fridge and leave to one side to soften.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them onto a #large baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop them onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel then set aside.

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the sweet potato has been in the oven for ~{10%minutes}, add the tomato parcel to the bottom shelf of your oven. Roast for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in #large frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and half the garlic, stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @water{100%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and lentils. Bring to the boil then lower the heat and simmer until reduced by about half, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the butter has softened slightly, pop into a #small bowl{} and add the remaining garlic. Use a #fork{} to mash the garlic into the butter. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} then spread the garlic butter over the cut sides.

Once the lentils have reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}. Simmer for a further ~{1%minute} then remove from the heat.

When there are about ~{5%minutes} of roasting time remaining, pop the ciabatta into the oven and bake until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When everything is ready, reheat the lentils (if needed), then stir in the sweet potato. Add a splash more @?water{} if you feel it needs it. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the creamy lentils out between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon the roasted tomatoes over the top, including any juices from the foil parcel.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} over the top. Finish by drizzling over the @mango chutney{40%g}.

Cut the garlic bread in half diagonally and serve alongside. Enjoy!